## 1. Headline verdict

**Verdict: `barcode_hypothesis_not_supported_at_phase_alpha`.** Pre-registered failure mode **F2 (aliasing)** triggered. 7 of 15 fixture pairs are indistinguishable on the chosen 12-slot vector.

The result is a **specific, actionable diagnosis**, not a refutation of the barcode hypothesis. The slot set was bimodal across two fixture families, and the slots chosen for the second family were precisely the ones we already knew from the lifted-singularity audit to be *structural invariants* — i.e., guaranteed to match across all fixtures of that class. The barcode framing still stands; Phase α revealed that the slot set needs cross-family coverage and empirical (not structural) slots in the lifted-singularity family.

